The paper focuses on the development of an interactive tool for guided clustering analysis, which is a common unsupervised learning method frequently used in exploratory data analysis. The tool is designed to help users effectively explore and navigate the large clustering space, improve the speed and effectiveness of exploratory clustering analysis, and facilitate the interpretation of clusters. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DB (Databases), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
